1
00:02:56,240 --> 00:02:57,440
Help…

2
00:03:01,320 --> 00:03:02,640
<i>I told you before.</i>

3
00:03:03,680 --> 00:03:05,360
I'd repay you. A life for a life.

4
00:03:06,240 --> 00:03:08,080
I'm going to make you my son.

5
00:03:09,640 --> 00:03:11,200
<i>Not just my adopted son,</i>

6
00:03:12,720 --> 00:03:14,960
<i>but Wayu Buranachat.</i>

7
00:03:15,040 --> 00:03:16,480
<i>Has no one ever told you</i>

8
00:03:17,080 --> 00:03:20,200
<i>that at the place you're standing,</i>
<i>someone died right there?</i>

9
00:03:20,280 --> 00:03:22,240
Did you know anything
about the house's background?

10
00:03:22,320 --> 00:03:23,560
The actress started talking.

11
00:03:24,400 --> 00:03:27,640
<i>But the Jaiaree family issue</i>
<i>has been quiet for so long.</i>

12
00:03:28,840 --> 00:03:32,000
<i>Why did the Mad Dog page bring this up?</i>

13
00:03:32,080 --> 00:03:33,920
We might still find a witness.

14
00:03:34,000 --> 00:03:37,320
<i>Someone transported a suspect with</i>
<i>a gunshot wound to the suspect area.</i>

15
00:03:37,400 --> 00:03:39,680
Black Doc’s gang won’t get away this time.

16
00:03:54,520 --> 00:03:55,680
Titan!

17
00:03:55,760 --> 00:03:58,360
- Don't do that to the officer.
- Get him off me, please.

18
00:03:58,440 --> 00:04:00,000
Hurry.

19
00:04:00,080 --> 00:04:02,240
- Hey.
- Titan, don't tease the officer.

20
00:04:04,160 --> 00:04:07,400
Joy! Joy, come take him out.

21
00:04:10,320 --> 00:04:13,920
I think we should step out first,
before another dog jumps on you.

22
00:04:15,120 --> 00:04:17,240
This way, please.

23
00:04:31,200 --> 00:04:32,040
He's gone?

24
00:04:32,120 --> 00:04:33,280
Yeah.

25
00:04:35,120 --> 00:04:37,800
Why didn't you hide
in a room you could lock?

26
00:04:41,760 --> 00:04:45,400
That was close. Good thing Titan helped.

27
00:04:48,040 --> 00:04:51,080
Sorry for almost
dragging you into trouble.

28
00:04:51,720 --> 00:04:52,880
Why apologize?

29
00:04:53,400 --> 00:04:55,120
We're family.

30
00:04:57,240 --> 00:04:58,600
We help each other.

31
00:04:59,960 --> 00:05:03,040
Besides, no matter how much trouble it is,

32
00:05:03,120 --> 00:05:05,320
I'll always stand by you.

33
00:05:07,040 --> 00:05:08,040
Thanks.

34
00:05:08,640 --> 00:05:10,760
How did the surgery go?

35
00:05:11,760 --> 00:05:12,840
It went well.

36
00:05:14,880 --> 00:05:16,680
But the police got this close.

37
00:05:17,920 --> 00:05:20,280
Next time, we'll need
somewhere more secure.

38
00:05:26,640 --> 00:05:29,000
You should take a good look at yourselves.

39
00:05:29,080 --> 00:05:32,040
You can't even catch
a single illegal doctor.

40
00:05:33,080 --> 00:05:35,440
We don't even know who he really is.

41
00:05:35,520 --> 00:05:37,080
Useless!

42
00:05:38,120 --> 00:05:40,160
You don't deserve to be cops.

43
00:05:44,920 --> 00:05:47,360
I'm giving you one last chance.

44
00:05:49,920 --> 00:05:51,040
Especially you.

45
00:05:52,560 --> 00:05:56,480
If you can't put him behind bars
within three months,

46
00:05:57,440 --> 00:05:59,200
prepare to be frozen out.

47
00:06:11,120 --> 00:06:15,000
<i>Impossible. I shot him myself.</i>

48
00:06:23,800 --> 00:06:25,200
I'm sorry.

49
00:06:25,920 --> 00:06:29,280
I'll finish the job this time.
I won't miss again.

50
00:06:37,040 --> 00:06:38,000
Sir.

51
00:06:40,800 --> 00:06:42,360
How the hell did Chun survive?

52
00:06:43,120 --> 00:06:46,600
Are you sure he isn't dead?

53
00:06:46,680 --> 00:06:49,960
Yes, sir. Word is
there's a skilled doctor.

54
00:06:50,040 --> 00:06:51,920
Everyone he treats survives.

55
00:06:52,000 --> 00:06:54,280
Everyone calls him Black Doc.

56
00:06:54,360 --> 00:06:57,080
He treats gangsters
and criminals for free.

57
00:06:58,520 --> 00:06:59,800
A doctor?

58
00:07:00,520 --> 00:07:04,160
Raka is the best med student in his class.

59
00:07:05,160 --> 00:07:09,120
No, in the whole faculty.
Even the professors say

60
00:07:09,200 --> 00:07:13,640
it's rare to see someone that talented.

61
00:07:19,640 --> 00:07:20,640
Sir,

62
00:07:20,720 --> 00:07:22,680
we couldn't find Peeraka's body.

63
00:07:22,760 --> 00:07:25,040
What? But I saw…

64
00:07:29,560 --> 00:07:33,480
Get anyone's body and say it's Peeraka's.

65
00:07:34,440 --> 00:07:35,880
We need a body.

66
00:07:36,520 --> 00:07:37,680
Yes, sir.

67
00:07:43,040 --> 00:07:44,440
Where the hell did the body go?

68
00:07:46,800 --> 00:07:50,960
I'll find out if Black Doc is you,

69
00:07:51,600 --> 00:07:53,360
Peeraka.

70
00:08:02,640 --> 00:08:03,800
Dad.

71
00:08:09,040 --> 00:08:11,040
I want to know about the Jaiaree.

72
00:08:14,960 --> 00:08:18,680
Hey. The news about Mr. Mahasamut
saving that woman,

73
00:08:18,760 --> 00:08:21,120
people are obsessed.

74
00:08:21,200 --> 00:08:24,320
They all want to be you right now.

75
00:08:24,840 --> 00:08:25,800
That much?

76
00:08:25,880 --> 00:08:30,920
Of course. A client actually reached out,
asking you to do a commercial together.

77
00:08:31,000 --> 00:08:34,559
But well, someone at his level probably
wouldn't take jobs like that anyway.

78
00:08:34,640 --> 00:08:39,200
So they'd adjust the script and have
you say,

79
00:08:39,280 --> 00:08:42,840
"After using this product,
my boyfriend loves me even more."

80
00:08:42,919 --> 00:08:44,360
I'm blushing just thinking about it.

81
00:08:45,480 --> 00:08:46,440
Oh.

82
00:08:47,280 --> 00:08:49,480
Whose food support is that?

83
00:08:50,000 --> 00:08:51,640
Oh? Isn't it mine?

84
00:08:52,320 --> 00:08:56,160
No. Your fanbase didn't say anything.

85
00:08:56,240 --> 00:08:59,280
And this is a private location.

86
00:08:59,360 --> 00:09:00,920
You said not to set anything up here

87
00:09:01,000 --> 00:09:03,000
out of respect for the homeowner.

88
00:09:06,520 --> 00:09:09,880
- So whose is it?
- No need to wonder.

89
00:09:09,960 --> 00:09:11,520
Here it is.

90
00:09:11,600 --> 00:09:13,640
Flowers here.

91
00:09:13,720 --> 00:09:15,440
- Thank you.
- Alright.

92
00:09:16,080 --> 00:09:18,760
The homeowner said he's a fan of yours,

93
00:09:18,840 --> 00:09:23,000
so he arranged food support
and flowers to cheer you on.

94
00:09:24,640 --> 00:09:25,800
Your fan.

95
00:09:27,160 --> 00:09:28,680
Come on. Let's go get you ready.

96
00:09:28,760 --> 00:09:29,960
- Let's go.
- Yes.

97
00:09:31,320 --> 00:09:35,000
It's just political games
from the opposition.

98
00:09:35,080 --> 00:09:36,280
That's all.

99
00:09:37,320 --> 00:09:39,680
And I'm sure it's them.

100
00:09:41,640 --> 00:09:44,720
They're trying to discredit me and Dad

101
00:09:45,520 --> 00:09:47,880
to win the election this year.

102
00:09:49,320 --> 00:09:53,600
So that Mad Dog page is working with them?

103
00:09:53,680 --> 00:09:55,800
<i>We don't have proof.</i>

104
00:09:56,920 --> 00:09:58,440
<i>But politics</i>

105
00:09:59,040 --> 00:10:00,680
<i>is like this.</i>

106
00:10:01,400 --> 00:10:05,080
<i>You know the case was closed long ago.</i>

107
00:10:05,160 --> 00:10:11,200
And suddenly, these people dig it back up
and start accusing us just because

108
00:10:11,280 --> 00:10:13,120
we turned that house into a foundation?

109
00:10:14,920 --> 00:10:18,720
They're using media influence
to manipulate

110
00:10:18,800 --> 00:10:20,320
the public however they want.

111
00:10:21,360 --> 00:10:25,280
So why did we use that land
to set up the foundation?

112
00:10:25,880 --> 00:10:28,760
After the incident,

113
00:10:28,840 --> 00:10:31,640
it became a hangout for drug addicts.

114
00:10:33,200 --> 00:10:36,840
Sometimes even those
ghost-hunting thrill seekers showed up.

115
00:10:36,920 --> 00:10:40,800
The locals felt unsafe,
so they filed complaints.

116
00:10:40,880 --> 00:10:44,400
That's why Samut and I bought the house
and turned it into a foundation

117
00:10:44,480 --> 00:10:48,440
to help people and support the community.

118
00:10:49,200 --> 00:10:50,360
That's all.

119
00:10:51,760 --> 00:10:56,840
I never thought anyone would link us
to old issues just to discredit us.

120
00:11:00,360 --> 00:11:01,840
You ended up getting dragged into it.

121
00:11:04,440 --> 00:11:05,640
I'm fine.

122
00:11:07,080 --> 00:11:08,680
I'm more worried about you and Dad.

123
00:11:09,480 --> 00:11:13,600
If we've done nothing wrong,
then we'll fight this to the end.

124
00:11:13,680 --> 00:11:15,600
Let everyone know the truth.

125
00:11:30,240 --> 00:11:32,800
Well said, Fahsai.

126
00:11:36,200 --> 00:11:37,160
Yes.

127
00:11:38,680 --> 00:11:40,640
Everyone will know the truth.

128
00:11:46,000 --> 00:11:49,680
<i>Deceptive Love</i>,
scene 19, cut one, take one.

129
00:11:49,760 --> 00:11:50,960
Go.

130
00:11:51,040 --> 00:11:54,840
All these lies have to end.

131
00:11:54,920 --> 00:11:57,240
This is the truth.

132
00:12:38,040 --> 00:12:39,040
Are you alright?

133
00:12:42,160 --> 00:12:43,360
You…

134
00:12:47,240 --> 00:12:49,480
I'm fine. Thank you.

135
00:12:52,640 --> 00:12:54,080
How could something like this happen?

136
00:12:54,680 --> 00:12:56,360
What if you got hurt?

137
00:12:57,840 --> 00:13:01,000
We've filmed so many action scenes
with this crew.

138
00:13:01,080 --> 00:13:02,680
Nothing's ever gone wrong before.

139
00:13:03,760 --> 00:13:07,120
Yiwa, isn't it your job
to take care of May?

140
00:13:07,200 --> 00:13:09,520
Why are you defending the crew?

141
00:13:13,680 --> 00:13:16,840
May, are you really okay?

142
00:13:19,600 --> 00:13:23,920
I'm okay. Just a bit shaken.

143
00:13:25,440 --> 00:13:27,040
I'll take care of Maysa myself.

144
00:13:28,200 --> 00:13:31,080
That's my responsibility. I know.

145
00:13:36,200 --> 00:13:39,600
So, why did you come all the way here?

146
00:13:39,680 --> 00:13:41,240
Is there anything you need?

147
00:13:43,200 --> 00:13:46,600
I wanted to ask about the Mad Dog page.

148
00:13:49,160 --> 00:13:52,440
Why are they dragging you into this?
I don't understand.

149
00:13:56,560 --> 00:13:58,480
You believe that kind of news?

150
00:13:59,280 --> 00:14:00,600
They're nobodies,

151
00:14:00,680 --> 00:14:04,080
just making things up.

152
00:14:09,600 --> 00:14:11,800
They're probably linking me

153
00:14:11,880 --> 00:14:15,440
because I'm close to Mr. Samut.
That's all.

154
00:14:17,680 --> 00:14:20,600
But it still feels strange.

155
00:14:20,680 --> 00:14:22,080
It's not.

156
00:14:22,160 --> 00:14:25,160
Fake news is everywhere these days.

157
00:14:25,880 --> 00:14:28,000
Instead of questioning that,

158
00:14:28,080 --> 00:14:30,800
shouldn't we focus on protecting Maysa?

159
00:14:35,120 --> 00:14:38,000
That's not what I meant. But…

160
00:14:41,360 --> 00:14:42,200
Excuse me.

161
00:14:54,840 --> 00:14:56,360
Where did he go?

162
00:15:01,760 --> 00:15:02,680
Hey!

163
00:15:03,680 --> 00:15:05,040
Why so startled?

164
00:15:07,440 --> 00:15:09,040
You were looking for me, weren't you?

165
00:15:10,880 --> 00:15:12,400
I…

166
00:15:14,440 --> 00:15:15,840
What are you doing here?

167
00:15:18,360 --> 00:15:19,920
And why can't I be here?

168
00:15:20,680 --> 00:15:22,320
This is a film set.

169
00:15:22,400 --> 00:15:25,880
Even if you're a fan, you shouldn't
interfere with people's work.

170
00:15:27,680 --> 00:15:29,880
If I hadn't interfered,

171
00:15:29,960 --> 00:15:32,320
what do you think
would've happened to Ms. Maysa?

172
00:15:38,280 --> 00:15:41,120
Don't you think
you're judging me a bit too harshly,

173
00:15:42,000 --> 00:15:43,240
Ms. Fahsai?

174
00:15:44,760 --> 00:15:46,200
You know me?

175
00:15:47,680 --> 00:15:48,560
Of course.

176
00:15:49,280 --> 00:15:51,400
You and your family are famous now.

177
00:15:51,480 --> 00:15:53,080
Everyone keeps talking about you.

178
00:15:53,920 --> 00:15:55,080
By the way,

179
00:15:56,000 --> 00:15:59,800
how does it feel to become…

180
00:16:01,400 --> 00:16:03,640
infamous overnight?

181
00:16:08,560 --> 00:16:09,640
Does it hurt?

182
00:16:10,600 --> 00:16:12,120
You should get that treated.

183
00:16:14,720 --> 00:16:16,080
I'll inform the crew.

184
00:16:17,720 --> 00:16:19,480
Are all politicians like this?

185
00:16:23,160 --> 00:16:27,040
Even their kids
always pretend to be good to fool people.

186
00:16:28,920 --> 00:16:30,840
Do you have some issue with politicians?

187
00:16:31,440 --> 00:16:33,240
Why do you keep talking like that?

188
00:16:36,840 --> 00:16:38,280
Maybe…

189
00:16:39,120 --> 00:16:40,040
it really was my fault.

190
00:16:43,200 --> 00:16:45,840
Even if you were stalking May,

191
00:16:46,800 --> 00:16:48,600
you're hurt like this,

192
00:16:51,000 --> 00:16:54,200
I shouldn't have blamed you.
I should thank you instead.

193
00:16:57,560 --> 00:16:58,960
Thank you.

194
00:17:03,360 --> 00:17:06,599
But about you following May,
I won't ignore it.

195
00:17:10,400 --> 00:17:12,359
I'll have someone bring you some medicine.

196
00:17:21,520 --> 00:17:22,480
Okay.

197
00:17:22,560 --> 00:17:25,319
I've already sent someone
to treat Mr. Wayu's wound.

198
00:17:25,400 --> 00:17:26,800
Thanks for informing us.

199
00:17:26,880 --> 00:17:29,240
I'm going back to work now.

200
00:17:29,320 --> 00:17:30,520
Wait.

201
00:17:32,280 --> 00:17:33,880
There's something else.

202
00:17:34,960 --> 00:17:37,640
The crew shouldn't allow him on set.

203
00:17:38,640 --> 00:17:42,000
I don't know what right he has.
Maybe he claims to be a fan.

204
00:17:42,600 --> 00:17:44,800
But he's followed May before.

205
00:17:47,120 --> 00:17:51,000
Even if he helped May this time,
I don't think we should let him

206
00:17:51,080 --> 00:17:53,280
get close to her whenever he wants.

207
00:17:53,360 --> 00:17:56,960
It's your responsibility
to ensure the actors'safety.

208
00:17:58,280 --> 00:18:00,640
And how exactly is Mr. Wayu unsafe?

209
00:18:04,080 --> 00:18:07,840
I think he's a stalker.

210
00:18:07,920 --> 00:18:08,960
Huh?

211
00:18:10,320 --> 00:18:13,360
Mr. Wayu, the owner
of this house, is a stalker?

212
00:18:14,560 --> 00:18:15,880
The owner?

213
00:18:15,960 --> 00:18:17,120
Huh?

214
00:18:17,200 --> 00:18:19,520
Mr. Wayu, the owner
of Mr. Chaichana's house?

215
00:18:20,160 --> 00:18:23,240
That means he's the heir

216
00:18:23,320 --> 00:18:25,880
of the former top mafia of Thonburi?

217
00:18:25,960 --> 00:18:28,640
Seriously? He's that young?

218
00:18:31,000 --> 00:18:33,600
They said he's brutal.
I thought he'd look like a gangster.

219
00:18:36,120 --> 00:18:38,440
He's so handsome in person.

220
00:18:43,920 --> 00:18:48,200
I think there's been a misunderstanding.

221
00:18:49,120 --> 00:18:50,920
He doesn't mean any harm.

222
00:18:51,000 --> 00:18:54,040
He even let us use this house
for filming for free.

223
00:18:56,280 --> 00:19:00,240
So you're risking the actors' safety
just to save the budget?

224
00:19:04,480 --> 00:19:07,560
Letting you film here for free
is even more suspicious than stalking.

225
00:19:14,880 --> 00:19:17,840
Hey. Thank you again,

226
00:19:17,920 --> 00:19:21,600
but please stop trying
to get close to May like this.

227
00:19:24,280 --> 00:19:25,360
That won't be possible.

228
00:19:28,280 --> 00:19:30,880
See? He admitted it.
Everyone heard that, right?

229
00:19:33,360 --> 00:19:34,800
Yes.

230
00:19:37,440 --> 00:19:40,120
I can't stop getting close to Ms. Maysa.

231
00:19:45,040 --> 00:19:46,480
People these days…

232
00:19:53,720 --> 00:19:55,160
At least you have the guts

233
00:19:57,200 --> 00:19:58,800
to admit it.

234
00:20:02,040 --> 00:20:05,640
So you'll do what I asked, right?

235
00:20:07,160 --> 00:20:09,040
Keep him away from May.

236
00:20:11,680 --> 00:20:13,760
Wayu wouldn't do that.

237
00:20:21,560 --> 00:20:24,120
He would never think like that.

238
00:20:24,200 --> 00:20:26,160
I can guarantee it.

239
00:20:26,240 --> 00:20:27,760
Because actually,

240
00:20:28,360 --> 00:20:30,360
I'm the one who's a fan of Ms.Maysa.

241
00:20:37,120 --> 00:20:39,920
I was the one who asked Wayu
to talk to Ms. Maysa.

242
00:20:40,000 --> 00:20:43,040
And I'm also the one
who let the crew film at our house.

243
00:20:44,040 --> 00:20:46,360
He's super busy,

244
00:20:46,440 --> 00:20:48,520
but still makes time to help.

245
00:20:48,600 --> 00:20:50,520
He's the sweetest.

246
00:20:53,960 --> 00:20:54,800
Wow.

247
00:21:00,720 --> 00:21:05,600
I'm Prapai, his younger sister.
I've watched all your dramas.

248
00:21:06,200 --> 00:21:08,160
Can we take a photo together?

249
00:21:09,280 --> 00:21:11,320
- Of course.
- Thank you.

250
00:21:13,720 --> 00:21:16,920
Well, can you take the photo for us?

251
00:21:23,200 --> 00:21:24,320
Thank you.

252
00:21:48,080 --> 00:21:50,680
I really don't trust that man.

253
00:21:51,520 --> 00:21:55,120
He's not ordinary, and being
a mafia son makes it even worse.

254
00:21:55,200 --> 00:21:58,040
Maysa probably
isn't interested in him anyway.

255
00:21:59,000 --> 00:21:59,840
Samut,

256
00:22:00,600 --> 00:22:02,640
I know you trust May.

257
00:22:03,240 --> 00:22:05,760
I'm not saying she'd cheat.

258
00:22:06,360 --> 00:22:10,480
But having a strange guy around
your girlfriend doesn't bother you at all?

259
00:22:11,080 --> 00:22:12,120
Look.

260
00:22:12,920 --> 00:22:14,480
She's an actress.

261
00:22:14,560 --> 00:22:18,640
This kind of thing happens.
Nothing strange.

262
00:22:19,800 --> 00:22:20,960
Don't overthink it.

263
00:22:23,240 --> 00:22:26,640
That guy only bothered Maysa,

264
00:22:27,560 --> 00:22:29,480
not you, right?

265
00:22:34,160 --> 00:22:35,640
I don't think so.

266
00:22:39,120 --> 00:22:40,200
Good then.

267
00:22:45,440 --> 00:22:47,280
But if he ever crosses the line with you,

268
00:22:49,320 --> 00:22:50,640
tell me.

269
00:22:52,800 --> 00:22:55,720
Oh my.

270
00:22:55,800 --> 00:22:59,120
Mr. Samut, you're such a sweet <i>oppa</i>.

271
00:22:59,200 --> 00:23:01,520
A protective brother.

272
00:23:09,440 --> 00:23:11,400
Are you talking about Mr. Wayu?

273
00:23:14,640 --> 00:23:17,760
I thought you were just being considerate
and didn't want to say it,

274
00:23:17,840 --> 00:23:19,120
so I spoke up for you.

275
00:23:22,040 --> 00:23:24,440
What Mr. Samut said is right.

276
00:23:24,520 --> 00:23:25,960
I'm an actress.

277
00:23:26,040 --> 00:23:29,200
I can handle this easily.
Nothing to worry about.

278
00:23:34,120 --> 00:23:37,800
Actually, I should be thanking Mr. Wayu

279
00:23:38,400 --> 00:23:40,720
for risking himself to save me.

280
00:23:43,040 --> 00:23:44,600
Should I invite him out to thank him?

281
00:23:46,440 --> 00:23:48,080
Sounds good. Go ahead.

282
00:23:50,440 --> 00:23:51,480
Okay.

283
00:23:55,440 --> 00:23:57,400
What kind of boyfriend is that? Useless.

284
00:23:58,800 --> 00:24:02,680
You shielded her from the effect
and he doesn't even thank you?

285
00:24:03,680 --> 00:24:05,160
What do you expect from them?

286
00:24:06,120 --> 00:24:07,360
Politicians are like this.

287
00:24:07,440 --> 00:24:09,120
They only do things
that make them look good.

288
00:24:11,600 --> 00:24:14,600
But in about two hours…

289
00:24:16,040 --> 00:24:17,600
they'll be thanking me themselves.

290
00:24:37,880 --> 00:24:39,560
- Wow.
- What is this?

291
00:24:39,640 --> 00:24:41,240
Damn.

292
00:24:47,200 --> 00:24:50,240
So cute.

293
00:25:13,400 --> 00:25:14,280
Hello.

294
00:25:17,600 --> 00:25:19,800
Mr. Mahasamut's secretary?

295
00:25:21,400 --> 00:25:22,880
Yes. How can I help?

296
00:25:28,840 --> 00:25:32,720
Mr. Mahasamut wants to meet me
and thank me?

297
00:25:38,280 --> 00:25:39,240
My pleasure.

298
00:25:41,360 --> 00:25:43,080
Of course. Goodbye.

299
00:25:46,880 --> 00:25:47,760
Seriously?

300
00:26:35,880 --> 00:26:38,000
Is that a house or a clubhouse?

301
00:26:38,080 --> 00:26:39,120
Sir,

302
00:26:40,040 --> 00:26:41,600
Mr. Wayu is here.

303
00:27:04,320 --> 00:27:07,240
You know what this is, right?

304
00:27:07,760 --> 00:27:09,000
Hey!

305
00:27:09,080 --> 00:27:10,760
Raka, run!

306
00:27:10,840 --> 00:27:12,520
Run!

307
00:27:15,200 --> 00:27:16,520
Kul!

308
00:27:16,600 --> 00:27:17,920
Kul!

309
00:27:18,440 --> 00:27:19,720
Kul!

310
00:27:36,600 --> 00:27:37,680
Mr. Wayu.

311
00:27:40,960 --> 00:27:42,800
Thank you for coming.

312
00:27:48,400 --> 00:27:49,680
I'm Mahasamut.

313
00:28:03,480 --> 00:28:04,800
I'm Wayu.

314
00:28:07,160 --> 00:28:08,600
Nice to meet you.

315
00:28:11,160 --> 00:28:15,280
Actually, I should've been
the one to meet you.

316
00:28:16,240 --> 00:28:21,120
But I already had a golf appointment
with my group, so you had to come here.

317
00:28:22,240 --> 00:28:23,560
Hope you don't mind.

318
00:28:24,080 --> 00:28:27,600
I don't care who meets whom first.

319
00:28:27,680 --> 00:28:32,520
Just getting the chance to meet
a representative as busy as you

320
00:28:33,760 --> 00:28:35,600
is already my good fortune.

321
00:28:37,000 --> 00:28:40,280
About you helping Maysa,
thank you very much.

322
00:28:41,080 --> 00:28:42,280
It was nothing.

323
00:28:42,920 --> 00:28:43,880
Good.

324
00:28:45,240 --> 00:28:50,120
In that case, if there's anything
I can do to repay you, just say so.

325
00:28:50,200 --> 00:28:52,440
I'd just like the chance
to play golf with you.

326
00:28:55,000 --> 00:28:57,240
That would be an honor for me.

327
00:28:58,400 --> 00:28:59,280
Good.

328
00:29:00,640 --> 00:29:02,320
Then let's enjoy it.

329
00:29:04,440 --> 00:29:08,960
But I won't count this as repayment.

330
00:29:20,440 --> 00:29:21,560
Your right hip is too high.

331
00:29:24,920 --> 00:29:26,440
Want me to help?

332
00:29:26,520 --> 00:29:27,680
Yes.

333
00:29:29,080 --> 00:29:30,200
Excuse me.

334
00:29:36,440 --> 00:29:37,720
Good.

335
00:29:46,240 --> 00:29:47,480
Excuse me.

336
00:29:51,160 --> 00:29:53,320
Your right hip is too high.

337
00:29:53,400 --> 00:29:56,640
When you downswing,
it makes you slice or top the ball.

338
00:30:05,080 --> 00:30:07,480
Keep your head still,
then turn down and press.

339
00:30:11,680 --> 00:30:12,920
Like that.

340
00:30:13,680 --> 00:30:15,480
- Okay.
- Try again.

341
00:30:22,480 --> 00:30:23,440
Beautiful.

342
00:30:25,760 --> 00:30:27,640
That really does feel better.

343
00:30:30,720 --> 00:30:33,920
I didn't realize you were here already,
so I didn't get to welcome you.

344
00:30:34,960 --> 00:30:38,000
It's fine. Early or late,

345
00:30:38,840 --> 00:30:40,000
as long as I get to see you,

346
00:30:40,800 --> 00:30:42,280
my whole day feels fresh.

347
00:30:45,440 --> 00:30:48,440
I heard your arm was hurt. How is it?

348
00:30:49,040 --> 00:30:51,520
It's nothing. Far from the heart.

349
00:30:52,720 --> 00:30:54,200
May I see it?

350
00:30:54,800 --> 00:30:56,120
I'm the reason you got hurt.

351
00:30:56,920 --> 00:31:00,320
I should take responsibility somehow.
At least for the medical expenses.

352
00:31:00,400 --> 00:31:02,160
That's nothing too.

353
00:31:02,760 --> 00:31:05,320
Don't worry about it. I'm fine.

354
00:31:06,320 --> 00:31:07,960
Well, if it's really nothing serious,

355
00:31:08,800 --> 00:31:09,960
then you should let me see it.

356
00:31:18,840 --> 00:31:20,040
A scar…

357
00:31:21,240 --> 00:31:22,440
What about it?

358
00:31:25,400 --> 00:31:27,120
Your scar…

359
00:31:27,760 --> 00:31:29,040
You're surprised?

360
00:31:33,520 --> 00:31:36,280
I'm a person with a lot of scars.

361
00:31:38,480 --> 00:31:41,440
Who did this to you?
That must have hurt so much.

362
00:31:43,720 --> 00:31:45,600
So you're here.

363
00:31:45,680 --> 00:31:47,040
Yes.

364
00:31:51,080 --> 00:31:54,960
I saw Ms. Maysa practicing her swing,
so I came over to say hello.

365
00:31:55,040 --> 00:31:59,680
Well, Maysa feels very grateful to you.

366
00:31:59,760 --> 00:32:01,360
So do I.

367
00:32:01,960 --> 00:32:04,960
I happened to see the reporters
looking for the hero,

368
00:32:05,640 --> 00:32:07,120
so I offered to bring them here.

369
00:32:10,840 --> 00:32:12,760
Then why don't we take a photo together?

370
00:32:14,760 --> 00:32:15,840
With pleasure.

371
00:32:15,920 --> 00:32:17,360
Fahsai, come here.

372
00:32:21,000 --> 00:32:22,240
This way, please.

373
00:32:22,320 --> 00:32:23,440
Look at this camera, please.

374
00:32:23,520 --> 00:32:24,960
- This way.
- This camera too, please.

375
00:32:33,000 --> 00:32:33,840
Excuse us.

376
00:32:33,920 --> 00:32:35,360
- Alright.
- Thank you.

377
00:32:37,040 --> 00:32:38,400
I think we should head to the tee-off.

378
00:32:38,480 --> 00:32:39,880
I'll follow in a bit.

379
00:32:41,040 --> 00:32:42,600
Okay, let's go.

380
00:32:42,680 --> 00:32:43,640
Yes.

381
00:33:01,360 --> 00:33:03,760
Is there something you need, Ms. Fahsai?

382
00:33:03,840 --> 00:33:05,240
You saw it, didn't you?

383
00:33:06,040 --> 00:33:08,400
Samut and Maysa
are being very kind to you.

384
00:33:09,880 --> 00:33:12,480
Even though he knows
you've been clinging to his girlfriend,

385
00:33:13,040 --> 00:33:14,680
he still thanked you

386
00:33:15,600 --> 00:33:17,000
and invited you to join the round.

387
00:33:17,880 --> 00:33:19,600
You're stuck on the stalker idea,
aren't you?

388
00:33:21,640 --> 00:33:22,880
My sister cleared that up.

389
00:33:24,240 --> 00:33:25,240
If that's true, then good.

390
00:33:26,120 --> 00:33:29,840
I hope you don't betray
the trust my brother has in you.

391
00:33:35,800 --> 00:33:37,160
You're quite obsessed…

392
00:33:39,560 --> 00:33:41,240
with your brother, aren't you?

393
00:33:43,040 --> 00:33:44,280
There's nothing strange about that.

394
00:33:45,040 --> 00:33:47,280
Your sister clearly loves you a lot too.

395
00:33:49,320 --> 00:33:50,920
She might even be helping you.

396
00:33:52,680 --> 00:33:53,520
That's true.

397
00:33:54,520 --> 00:33:56,560
Siblings help each other. It's normal.

398
00:33:59,000 --> 00:34:01,080
But since you studied law

399
00:34:01,800 --> 00:34:03,080
and run a foundation,

400
00:34:04,160 --> 00:34:05,400
let me ask you something.

401
00:34:07,120 --> 00:34:09,679
Between siblings and what's right,

402
00:34:10,239 --> 00:34:11,239
if you had to choose,

403
00:34:11,840 --> 00:34:12,800
which would you choose?

404
00:34:15,600 --> 00:34:16,880
And beyond siblings,

405
00:34:18,920 --> 00:34:21,920
do you still have justice left
for other people?

406
00:34:28,840 --> 00:34:31,040
You make it sound like I'm playing
favorites and doing something wrong.

407
00:34:31,120 --> 00:34:32,280
What's your problem--

408
00:34:44,440 --> 00:34:45,320
No need.

409
00:34:50,159 --> 00:34:50,960
Hey!

410
00:34:53,120 --> 00:34:55,199
You fall right in front of me.

411
00:34:56,480 --> 00:34:58,760
Let me be a gentleman.

412
00:35:01,360 --> 00:35:02,440
Hey.

413
00:35:37,280 --> 00:35:38,560
Birdie.

414
00:35:49,320 --> 00:35:50,480
Show-off.

415
00:35:53,000 --> 00:35:56,400
I respect my opponent.
That's why I play at full capacity.

416
00:35:57,800 --> 00:36:00,560
Good. That's what makes it fun.

417
00:36:27,920 --> 00:36:29,080
Par.

418
00:36:30,640 --> 00:36:31,800
Good job.

419
00:36:46,640 --> 00:36:48,240
Thought you were better than that.

420
00:37:11,760 --> 00:37:13,720
Looks like luck isn't on your side.

421
00:37:18,520 --> 00:37:20,080
That's why I like golf.

422
00:37:20,160 --> 00:37:21,840
It's a long game.

423
00:37:23,560 --> 00:37:24,920
Every shot we hit,

424
00:37:25,960 --> 00:37:27,440
if there's still a chance,

425
00:37:27,520 --> 00:37:28,920
you can turn it around.

426
00:37:29,000 --> 00:37:31,880
That may be true.

427
00:37:33,880 --> 00:37:37,960
But most people, once they start missing
too often, find it hard to stay hopeful.

428
00:37:39,120 --> 00:37:40,960
That's why it reveals
who people really are.

429
00:37:43,920 --> 00:37:45,760
If I turn this around…

430
00:37:48,400 --> 00:37:50,560
I want the reward you promised.

431
00:37:56,920 --> 00:37:59,360
I'm a man of my word.

432
00:38:00,960 --> 00:38:05,320
It depends on whether
what you ask for isn't too much.

433
00:38:07,160 --> 00:38:10,040
I want to help you with your campaign
for the upcoming election.

434
00:38:11,640 --> 00:38:12,920
I want to be on your team.

435
00:38:23,520 --> 00:38:24,840
How about this?

436
00:38:27,160 --> 00:38:28,400
If you can finish with a par…

437
00:38:30,400 --> 00:38:31,240
then deal.

438
00:38:32,680 --> 00:38:35,400
Finishing with a par is tough.

439
00:38:35,480 --> 00:38:37,920
There's only one shot left.

440
00:38:49,520 --> 00:38:52,280
Samut, are you really going
to let him work with you?

441
00:39:02,840 --> 00:39:04,200
Sorry.

442
00:39:07,280 --> 00:39:10,960
Something urgent just came up.
I have to leave immediately.

443
00:39:17,160 --> 00:39:19,840
Let's do a rematch another time.

444
00:39:19,920 --> 00:39:22,640
I'm sorry I can't stay
until the end today.

445
00:39:27,680 --> 00:39:31,720
Seems like our luck
just isn't aligned yet.

446
00:39:33,160 --> 00:39:35,000
My luck probably isn't good enough yet.

447
00:39:35,720 --> 00:39:38,320
It's fine. Next time.

448
00:39:52,480 --> 00:39:54,400
You two go wait at the cart.

449
00:39:55,440 --> 00:39:56,480
Okay.

450
00:40:01,520 --> 00:40:02,560
Is everything settled?

451
00:40:03,200 --> 00:40:04,080
Yes, sir.

452
00:40:04,160 --> 00:40:05,840
I've booked a villa for the party

453
00:40:06,400 --> 00:40:09,840
and sent invitations to everyone,
except Wayu.

454
00:40:13,000 --> 00:40:15,640
So he wants to rely
on political influence?

455
00:40:15,720 --> 00:40:17,440
Those lowlifes. Keep dreaming.

456
00:40:19,680 --> 00:40:20,640
If I…

457
00:40:31,080 --> 00:40:33,040
Has Tarn left the party office yet?

458
00:40:33,680 --> 00:40:36,920
Our intel says he's nearing Muak Lek.

459
00:40:39,480 --> 00:40:42,800
<i>As for that Mad Dog page</i>
<i>exposing Peeraka's case,</i>

460
00:40:43,440 --> 00:40:47,440
<i>it's probably Tarn</i>
<i>or someone in his party.</i>

461
00:40:49,360 --> 00:40:50,560
Are you sure?

462
00:40:52,080 --> 00:40:55,680
If it's not him, then fine.

463
00:40:56,360 --> 00:40:58,840
Reporters love hyping him up anyway,

464
00:40:58,920 --> 00:41:02,280
calling him the idol
of the new generation.

465
00:41:05,120 --> 00:41:06,360
Just set him up.

466
00:41:08,640 --> 00:41:10,360
And don't mess up about Lena.

467
00:41:12,360 --> 00:41:13,280
Yes, sir.

468
00:41:23,280 --> 00:41:24,440
Those slimy bastards.

469
00:41:25,240 --> 00:41:28,480
The moment they're cornered,
they shamelessly run off.

470
00:41:28,560 --> 00:41:30,840
You should've told the reporters

471
00:41:31,600 --> 00:41:32,920
they deliberately bailed.

472
00:41:33,000 --> 00:41:35,400
We'll step into their territory
with dignity.

473
00:41:36,720 --> 00:41:38,720
I won't let them see us
as just stray dogs.

474
00:41:41,240 --> 00:41:42,520
I can wait.

475
00:41:49,760 --> 00:41:51,520
In that case,
you might not have to wait long.

476
00:42:00,400 --> 00:42:01,480
Listen to this.

477
00:42:05,240 --> 00:42:08,720
<i>As for that Mad Dog page</i>
<i>exposing Peeraka's case,</i>

478
00:42:09,440 --> 00:42:14,080
<i>it's probably Tarn</i>
<i>or someone in his party.</i>

479
00:42:30,600 --> 00:42:31,880
I still can't believe it.

480
00:42:33,240 --> 00:42:36,360
Someone like Mr. Tarn
wants to have dinner with me?

481
00:42:36,880 --> 00:42:38,400
His reputation is so clean.

482
00:42:40,520 --> 00:42:42,160
Exactly.

483
00:42:42,240 --> 00:42:44,400
That just proves my Lena

484
00:42:44,480 --> 00:42:46,680
is premium.

485
00:42:48,200 --> 00:42:49,520
Anyway,

486
00:42:49,600 --> 00:42:51,480
men are all the same.

487
00:42:51,560 --> 00:42:56,920
They want something beautiful
to admire and relax with.

488
00:42:58,600 --> 00:43:00,920
Are you sure it's really just dinner?

489
00:43:01,520 --> 00:43:02,920
Of course.

490
00:43:03,680 --> 00:43:04,680
Lena,

491
00:43:04,760 --> 00:43:07,320
how long have you worked with me already?

492
00:43:08,200 --> 00:43:09,720
Have I ever lied to you?

493
00:43:10,480 --> 00:43:12,880
Never. Or have I?

494
00:43:14,160 --> 00:43:15,840
No, never.

495
00:43:31,320 --> 00:43:32,240
Oh.

496
00:43:32,320 --> 00:43:33,760
Are your lips dry?

497
00:43:33,840 --> 00:43:36,360
You keep reapplying lipstick.
Here, have some water.

498
00:43:36,440 --> 00:43:37,360
Your cold drink.

499
00:43:37,440 --> 00:43:39,280
- Thank you.
- Drink it.

500
00:43:39,360 --> 00:43:40,360
Alright.

501
00:43:41,000 --> 00:43:43,320
I've prepared everything for you.

502
00:43:43,400 --> 00:43:47,320
Snacks and fruits you like.

503
00:44:06,880 --> 00:44:08,200
Lena?

504
00:44:08,840 --> 00:44:11,520
Lena, are you in there? Are you done yet?

505
00:44:13,360 --> 00:44:14,520
Hurry up.

506
00:44:14,600 --> 00:44:16,080
We're running out of time.

507
00:44:16,760 --> 00:44:18,000
She's still not done?

508
00:44:18,600 --> 00:44:20,160
If she were, would I be standing here?

509
00:44:21,280 --> 00:44:23,880
Alright, you stay here.
I'll go check myself.

510
00:44:23,960 --> 00:44:26,880
Lena! Lena!

511
00:44:26,960 --> 00:44:29,120
Why aren't you answering?

512
00:44:29,800 --> 00:44:33,160
I told you to wait
until we arrive at the resort.

513
00:44:33,880 --> 00:44:35,280
We're almost there.

514
00:44:45,920 --> 00:44:47,160
Hey!

515
00:44:48,320 --> 00:44:49,960
The restroom's empty!

516
00:44:50,040 --> 00:44:51,480
Where did she go?

517
00:44:51,560 --> 00:44:54,520
The restroom's empty. No one's in there.

518
00:44:54,600 --> 00:44:56,600
Oh my.

519
00:44:56,680 --> 00:44:58,320
Lena's gone.

520
00:44:58,400 --> 00:45:00,560
- Let's check over there.
- Find her! Hurry!

521
00:45:01,600 --> 00:45:02,960
Lena!

522
00:45:03,040 --> 00:45:04,600
Lena! There!

523
00:45:04,680 --> 00:45:08,480
Over there. Hurry up!

524
00:45:12,920 --> 00:45:13,960
Ms. Lena!

525
00:45:14,040 --> 00:45:15,440
Ms. Lena!

526
00:45:18,360 --> 00:45:19,600
Ms. Lena!

527
00:45:19,680 --> 00:45:21,560
- No!
- Hurry!

528
00:45:21,640 --> 00:45:22,560
Ms. Lena, come back.

529
00:45:22,640 --> 00:45:23,640
- Let go of me!
- Lena.

530
00:45:23,720 --> 00:45:25,480
- Let go! I said let go!
- Hold her.

531
00:45:25,560 --> 00:45:26,800
Wait, wait.

532
00:45:26,880 --> 00:45:27,960
Lena.

533
00:45:28,040 --> 00:45:29,040
Wait.

534
00:45:29,120 --> 00:45:30,680
Lena, why are you running from me?

535
00:45:30,760 --> 00:45:32,280
Listen to me.

536
00:45:32,360 --> 00:45:34,880
You tricked me! I'm going to the police!

537
00:45:36,120 --> 00:45:38,240
- Come here.
- Let go!

538
00:45:38,320 --> 00:45:40,720
- She slapped me?
- Help me!

539
00:45:40,800 --> 00:45:42,440
Help me!

540
00:45:42,520 --> 00:45:44,000
Lena.

541
00:45:48,120 --> 00:45:49,480
Help me!

542
00:45:49,560 --> 00:45:52,640
I've taken such good care of your face,

543
00:45:52,720 --> 00:45:56,600
and this is how you treat me?

544
00:45:56,680 --> 00:45:58,560
Take her!

545
00:45:58,640 --> 00:46:00,440
- You think you're tough?
- Help me!

546
00:46:00,520 --> 00:46:02,080
Someone help me!

547
00:46:02,160 --> 00:46:04,200
- Struggle all you want.
- Help me!

548
00:46:04,280 --> 00:46:07,640
I'll deal with you properly, Lena.

549
00:46:30,600 --> 00:46:31,440
Hello.

550
00:46:36,080 --> 00:46:37,080
What did you say?

551
00:46:38,520 --> 00:46:39,800
Lena got away?

552
00:46:39,880 --> 00:46:41,360
How?

553
00:46:43,040 --> 00:46:46,120
Go find her and drag her back.

554
00:46:46,200 --> 00:46:49,360
If you idiots can't even catch one woman,

555
00:46:51,680 --> 00:46:52,720
you know what that means.

556
00:46:53,640 --> 00:46:54,680
Right?

557
00:47:10,120 --> 00:47:11,240
Boom!

558
00:47:11,320 --> 00:47:13,920
TIMELINE OF FAMOUS ACTRESS'S DISAPPEARANCE

559
00:47:21,280 --> 00:47:23,200
<i>There are now rumors</i>

560
00:47:23,280 --> 00:47:24,760
<i>that the famous young actress Lena</i>

561
00:47:24,840 --> 00:47:26,560
<i>has been missing since last night.</i>

562
00:47:26,640 --> 00:47:28,000
<i>Her family has been unable to contact her.</i>

563
00:47:29,160 --> 00:47:31,760
<i>Police have received preliminary</i>
<i>information from her manager</i>

564
00:47:31,840 --> 00:47:33,200
<i>that she disappeared into a forest,</i>

565
00:47:33,280 --> 00:47:34,760
<i>and her fate is still unknown.</i>

566
00:47:34,840 --> 00:47:35,760
WILL MAD DOG HELP WITH THIS?

567
00:47:35,840 --> 00:47:38,560
<i>Not long after that,</i>
<i>the famous Mad Dog page</i>

568
00:47:38,640 --> 00:47:41,600
<i>posted a sequence of events</i>
<i>surrounding Lena's disappearance,</i>

569
00:47:41,680 --> 00:47:43,960
<i>claiming it was suspicious.</i>

570
00:47:44,560 --> 00:47:45,680
<i>The page cited inside information,</i>

571
00:47:45,760 --> 00:47:48,120
<i>saying it was a job arranged</i>
<i>without Lena's knowledge,</i>

572
00:47:48,200 --> 00:47:50,960
<i>which caused her to resist and vanish.</i>

573
00:47:51,040 --> 00:47:51,960
HELP MS. LENA

574
00:47:53,200 --> 00:47:55,080
<i>As of today,</i>

575
00:47:55,160 --> 00:47:57,280
<i>it has been a full seven days,</i>

576
00:47:57,360 --> 00:47:59,000
<i>and Lena is still missing.</i>

577
00:47:59,080 --> 00:48:01,880
<i>Many people now believe</i>
<i>she may be in danger.</i>

578
00:48:01,960 --> 00:48:03,440
<i>Meanwhile, the Mad Dog page</i>

579
00:48:03,520 --> 00:48:05,520
<i>has also implicated the person behind it</i>

580
00:48:05,600 --> 00:48:07,600
<i>as being a handsome politician.</i>

581
00:48:14,720 --> 00:48:16,360
This is going to destroy us.

582
00:48:16,440 --> 00:48:18,960
Someone wants to discredit us.

583
00:48:19,040 --> 00:48:21,240
They lured you to that resort.

584
00:48:21,320 --> 00:48:22,720
This kind of dirty game

585
00:48:23,840 --> 00:48:25,240
has to be Rakchart's people.

586
00:48:27,720 --> 00:48:28,640
Wiwat,

587
00:48:28,720 --> 00:48:32,240
after coordinating with the police
to search for that actress,

588
00:48:32,320 --> 00:48:33,680
what progress is there?

589
00:48:33,760 --> 00:48:36,480
Police have already
searched the whole area

590
00:48:36,560 --> 00:48:38,600
by land and by air,

591
00:48:38,680 --> 00:48:40,240
but they found no solid lead,

592
00:48:40,320 --> 00:48:43,600
except clothing her family confirmed

593
00:48:43,680 --> 00:48:48,560
she wore that day
and suspicious bloodstains.

594
00:48:48,640 --> 00:48:50,840
Those are still being examined.

595
00:48:52,800 --> 00:48:55,000
If the results show
it's really Lena's blood,

596
00:48:55,080 --> 00:48:57,760
or if they find a body, we're finished.

597
00:48:58,880 --> 00:49:00,600
That page has to be on Rakchart's side.

598
00:49:01,400 --> 00:49:02,960
They're deliberately framing us.

599
00:49:05,520 --> 00:49:07,600
The election is getting closer,

600
00:49:08,240 --> 00:49:11,560
and our approval is crashing
worse than a market collapse.

601
00:49:12,200 --> 00:49:13,880
What are we supposed to do?

602
00:49:15,280 --> 00:49:16,880
I'll hold a press conference.

603
00:49:16,960 --> 00:49:17,800
Wiwat,

604
00:49:18,560 --> 00:49:21,360
call the reporters.
I'm doing it this afternoon.

605
00:49:22,080 --> 00:49:22,920
Yes, sir.

606
00:49:24,920 --> 00:49:27,360
We really have to thank that Mad Dog page

607
00:49:27,440 --> 00:49:30,400
and the people who love justice so much.

608
00:49:34,520 --> 00:49:36,360
And did you send people
after that woman yet?

609
00:49:37,840 --> 00:49:39,360
Yes, Dad.

610
00:49:40,480 --> 00:49:44,280
But she ran into the forest like that,
so by now, she's probably dead.

611
00:49:46,080 --> 00:49:49,280
And if she's not, she will be.

612
00:49:51,560 --> 00:49:53,840
There's no way
she'll come back and say anything.

613
00:49:59,360 --> 00:50:02,000
Sir, Mr. Tarn is holding
a press conference.

614
00:50:04,880 --> 00:50:07,040
He's probably just going to claim

615
00:50:08,040 --> 00:50:10,240
he has nothing to do with it.

616
00:50:13,240 --> 00:50:15,440
- Jon.
- Yes, sir.

617
00:50:16,320 --> 00:50:19,240
Release the clip we have
while he's speaking.

618
00:50:22,520 --> 00:50:23,560
Yes, sir.

619
00:50:28,840 --> 00:50:30,200
What clip?

620
00:50:44,080 --> 00:50:45,000
This.

621
00:50:52,680 --> 00:50:53,560
Good.

622
00:50:54,240 --> 00:50:55,960
Clean it all up properly.

623
00:50:57,280 --> 00:51:00,640
We have to win the election
at the end of the year.

624
00:51:03,840 --> 00:51:07,200
I'd like to clarify
that this has nothing to do with me.

625
00:51:07,920 --> 00:51:09,280
I wasn't there that day.

626
00:51:10,400 --> 00:51:11,480
I…

627
00:51:11,560 --> 00:51:13,720
BREAKING NEWS!

628
00:51:13,800 --> 00:51:15,720
It's a video clip.

629
00:51:16,360 --> 00:51:17,600
Oh.

630
00:51:17,680 --> 00:51:19,720
Oh?

631
00:51:19,800 --> 00:51:25,920
OH? WHOSE CAR IS IT?

632
00:51:29,320 --> 00:51:33,360
Are you sure you weren't
at that resort that day?

633
00:51:33,440 --> 00:51:35,360
Then what is this clip?

634
00:51:36,680 --> 00:51:37,840
It shows

635
00:51:37,920 --> 00:51:40,920
your car and Lena's van
entering the same resort

636
00:51:41,000 --> 00:51:43,160
within a short time of each other.

637
00:51:43,240 --> 00:51:45,600
So did you go there or not?

638
00:51:46,320 --> 00:51:48,960
Or did you arrange for Lena
to take on hostess work?

639
00:51:49,040 --> 00:51:52,440
But you just said yourself
that you weren't there.

640
00:51:52,520 --> 00:51:54,720
I'm sorry I had to say that.

641
00:51:55,360 --> 00:51:57,920
I had an appointment with an important
person about confidential party matters.

642
00:51:58,480 --> 00:52:01,400
The party committee decided
I wasn't allowed to reveal that.

643
00:52:01,480 --> 00:52:04,240
Then how are people
supposed to believe you

644
00:52:04,320 --> 00:52:06,640
when all the evidence points to you?

645
00:52:06,720 --> 00:52:11,320
And how are you going to explain
that you're not involved in this?

646
00:52:12,240 --> 00:52:14,800
We have to end
the press conference here for now.

647
00:52:14,880 --> 00:52:16,520
Mr. Tarn has another meeting to attend.

648
00:52:18,000 --> 00:52:18,880
Wait.

649
00:52:18,960 --> 00:52:21,280
- Please give an interview.
- Are you involved in this case?

650
00:52:21,360 --> 00:52:22,960
Please make way.

651
00:52:23,040 --> 00:52:24,680
Where is Lena?

652
00:52:24,760 --> 00:52:26,920
Did you invite Lena there?

653
00:52:27,000 --> 00:52:28,160
I'm right here.

654
00:52:28,240 --> 00:52:29,400
Oh?

655
00:52:30,480 --> 00:52:31,320
Lena.

656
00:52:38,280 --> 00:52:39,320
Lena.

657
00:52:41,200 --> 00:52:42,760
Hey.

658
00:52:47,520 --> 00:52:50,320
So where exactly have you been?

659
00:52:51,240 --> 00:52:53,280
I don't think this is the time
to question her yet.

660
00:52:53,360 --> 00:52:56,360
Looking at her condition, I think
we should take her to the hospital first.

661
00:52:56,440 --> 00:52:58,480
So what exactly happened?

662
00:53:01,240 --> 00:53:02,760
Let's just say…

663
00:53:05,040 --> 00:53:08,400
a well-wisher sent me a warning message.

664
00:53:10,880 --> 00:53:12,800
And the reason I came here today

665
00:53:13,960 --> 00:53:16,760
is to confirm Mr. Tarn's innocence,

666
00:53:16,840 --> 00:53:19,080
that he has nothing to do with this.

667
00:53:19,600 --> 00:53:21,600
- Help me!
- You think you're tough?

668
00:53:21,680 --> 00:53:22,760
Anyone help me!

669
00:53:22,840 --> 00:53:25,280
- Go!
- Help me!

670
00:53:25,360 --> 00:53:27,160
Come here!

671
00:53:27,240 --> 00:53:28,480
Hey!

672
00:53:28,560 --> 00:53:30,080
- Come here.
- Hey!

673
00:53:30,160 --> 00:53:31,280
Stop!

674
00:53:31,360 --> 00:53:34,480
Please don't hurt me.

675
00:53:34,560 --> 00:53:35,600
No!

676
00:53:35,680 --> 00:53:37,560
It's okay.

677
00:53:37,640 --> 00:53:39,240
We're here to help you.

678
00:53:39,320 --> 00:53:41,400
Don't be scared.

679
00:53:41,480 --> 00:53:44,920
So your manager was secretly
accepting escort jobs for you?

680
00:53:46,160 --> 00:53:48,320
And if Mr. Tarn
had nothing to do with this,

681
00:53:48,400 --> 00:53:52,640
do you know who was really behind it?

682
00:53:55,640 --> 00:53:57,720
I'm not going to say anything right now.

683
00:53:58,240 --> 00:54:01,120
Please wait to hear it
from the Mad Dog page.

684
00:54:03,240 --> 00:54:04,200
Thank you.

685
00:54:10,520 --> 00:54:12,680
Excuse us. This way, Ms. Lena.

686
00:54:12,760 --> 00:54:15,400
Please give Lena some privacy. Please.

687
00:54:16,920 --> 00:54:18,240
How did this turn out like this?

688
00:54:18,320 --> 00:54:20,160
You can't handle
something this simple, Jon?

689
00:54:20,800 --> 00:54:22,520
Go tell your men.

690
00:54:22,600 --> 00:54:25,680
How the hell did they let her run away?

691
00:54:27,560 --> 00:54:28,480
Wait.

692
00:54:34,760 --> 00:54:38,960
Take some men and find out
where the Mad Dog page is based. Find them

693
00:54:39,040 --> 00:54:40,640
and smash the place to pieces.

694
00:54:41,280 --> 00:54:44,000
Don't let them get another chance
to say anything. Got it?

695
00:54:44,800 --> 00:54:45,840
Yes, sir.

696
00:54:45,920 --> 00:54:47,760
If you screw this up again,

697
00:54:49,440 --> 00:54:50,680
I won't spare you.

698
00:55:25,680 --> 00:55:28,240
It still looks as good as always, Mom.

699
00:55:28,320 --> 00:55:30,680
Of course. Same recipe.

700
00:55:30,760 --> 00:55:33,880
You used to love it.
These days, you hardly eat it anymore.

701
00:55:33,960 --> 00:55:35,280
It makes me fat.

702
00:55:35,360 --> 00:55:36,840
- Fat?
- Look at the sugar.

703
00:55:36,920 --> 00:55:39,280
- I already reduced the sugar.
- Look at it, Mom.

704
00:55:39,360 --> 00:55:41,840
- This is reduced sugar?
- Yes. Then eat it in the morning.

705
00:55:41,920 --> 00:55:45,200
- Fine. I'll save it for tomorrow.
- Yeah.

706
00:55:45,280 --> 00:55:46,800
Your brother likes this one too.

707
00:55:46,880 --> 00:55:49,880
- I don't know how he can eat so much.
- He gets hungry.

708
00:55:49,960 --> 00:55:52,080
- He rides the bus to school every day--
- Mom.

709
00:55:52,160 --> 00:55:53,840
You're back.

710
00:55:54,400 --> 00:55:56,480
- I'm back.
- He's back.

711
00:55:56,560 --> 00:55:57,960
Speak of the devil.

712
00:56:01,120 --> 00:56:02,480
What are you doing?

713
00:56:04,840 --> 00:56:06,600
Hey! How greedy.

714
00:56:06,680 --> 00:56:09,800
Why are you touching food
before washing your hands?

715
00:56:09,880 --> 00:56:11,400
How are you going
to become a doctor? So gross.

716
00:56:11,480 --> 00:56:12,840
I'm hungry.

717
00:56:12,920 --> 00:56:15,920
Don't scold him, Peekul.
Don't scold your brother.

718
00:56:16,000 --> 00:56:18,080
He's hungry, he's hungry.

719
00:56:18,160 --> 00:56:20,320
So? Were classes exhausting?

720
00:56:23,400 --> 00:56:25,320
The most exhausting in the world, Mom.

721
00:56:26,200 --> 00:56:30,040
You came from the hospital and you're
hugging Mom? You're bringing germs.

722
00:56:31,400 --> 00:56:32,880
Then I'll be the one to treat her.

723
00:56:34,640 --> 00:56:38,720
Graduate first, then talk.
I'm more worried you'll make her worse.

724
00:56:39,920 --> 00:56:42,560
- Mom, Kul's hitting me.
- Come on. Don't hurt him.

725
00:56:42,640 --> 00:56:45,280
He's mocking me. See? He's doing it again.

726
00:56:45,360 --> 00:56:46,800
See?

727
00:56:46,880 --> 00:56:49,000
Alright, alright.

728
00:57:15,480 --> 00:57:18,000
What exactly are you sitting here
smiling to yourself about?

729
00:57:25,520 --> 00:57:26,960
Is there a rule at this foundation

730
00:57:27,040 --> 00:57:29,280
that says no one else is allowed in?

731
00:57:31,880 --> 00:57:36,040
Or maybe I came to make merit
and donate money.

732
00:57:37,160 --> 00:57:38,080
Donate?

733
00:57:39,160 --> 00:57:40,640
You?

734
00:57:42,000 --> 00:57:45,400
Money earned from sin
doesn't count as merit.

735
00:57:48,480 --> 00:57:51,680
I just found out
that the chairwoman of this foundation

736
00:57:51,760 --> 00:57:54,120
is this narrow-minded.

737
00:57:56,040 --> 00:57:57,400
You think you're the good one,

738
00:57:58,440 --> 00:58:00,120
and you're using someone's profession

739
00:58:00,720 --> 00:58:03,640
to judge their worth as a human being,
who's good and who's bad.

740
00:58:08,560 --> 00:58:09,760
Let me tell you something.

741
00:58:10,800 --> 00:58:14,120
No matter the profession,
monks, police, teachers,

742
00:58:15,360 --> 00:58:17,240
there are good and bad people
amongst all of them.

743
00:58:19,560 --> 00:58:21,520
I know that. You don't need to lecture me.

744
00:58:23,360 --> 00:58:26,200
But I've never seen a mafia boss
who was a good person.

745
00:58:30,960 --> 00:58:32,160
Wait.

746
00:58:34,840 --> 00:58:36,360
What kind of scar is this?

747
00:58:41,960 --> 00:58:43,720
Just a hot-headed thug's scar.

748
00:58:45,960 --> 00:58:47,120
You wouldn't want to know.

749
00:59:00,440 --> 00:59:02,160
<i>Mr. Peeraka Jaiaree, the intern doctor</i>

750
00:59:02,240 --> 00:59:03,960
<i>who murdered his entire family,</i>

751
00:59:04,040 --> 00:59:06,400
<i>has died in a fire-related accident.</i>

752
00:59:06,480 --> 00:59:08,280
BODY OF INTERN DOCTOR
WHO KILLED HIS FAMILY FOUND

753
00:59:15,800 --> 00:59:17,000
Peeraka…

754
00:59:21,200 --> 00:59:24,240
I hope you'll be happy wherever you are.

755
00:59:25,960 --> 00:59:27,720
That man died a long time ago.

756
00:59:29,400 --> 00:59:33,040
Why do I keep connecting him to Wayu?

757
00:59:50,000 --> 00:59:51,240
What are they all looking at?

758
00:59:54,680 --> 00:59:56,840
Can we speak to Mr. Mahasamut?

759
00:59:56,920 --> 00:59:58,440
- Could we get an interview?
- Please.

760
00:59:58,520 --> 00:59:59,720
What's happening out there?

761
01:00:01,120 --> 01:00:02,280
Well…

762
01:00:03,760 --> 01:00:06,000
Why are you stalling? Just say it.

763
01:00:06,080 --> 01:00:08,200
The reporters are here
asking to interview you, sir.

764
01:00:10,080 --> 01:00:11,320
About what?

765
01:00:14,560 --> 01:00:17,560
There's an audio clip
the Mad Dog page just released.

766
01:00:23,560 --> 01:00:24,600
What clip?

767
01:00:26,680 --> 01:00:29,360
<i>As for that Mad Dog page</i>
<i>exposing Peeraka's case,</i>

768
01:00:29,960 --> 01:00:33,600
<i>it's probably Tarn</i>
<i>or someone in his party.</i>

769
01:00:33,680 --> 01:00:34,840
<i>Are you sure?</i>

770
01:00:34,920 --> 01:00:38,640
<i>If it's not him, then fine.</i>

771
01:00:38,720 --> 01:00:40,840
<i>Reporters love hyping him up anyway,</i>

772
01:00:40,920 --> 01:00:44,080
<i>calling him the idol</i>
<i>of the new generation.</i>

773
01:00:44,160 --> 01:00:45,520
<i>Just set him up.</i>

774
01:00:59,520 --> 01:01:01,560
So that is your voice on the clip,
Mr. Mahasamut?

775
01:01:01,640 --> 01:01:03,800
I can assure you,
that is absolutely not my voice.

776
01:01:03,880 --> 01:01:05,440
I have a way to prove it.

777
01:01:05,520 --> 01:01:07,120
- How?
- What way?

778
01:01:12,320 --> 01:01:13,520
Mr. Wayu,

779
01:01:14,120 --> 01:01:16,760
do you have any way
to help Fahsai become stronger?

780
01:01:26,600 --> 01:01:27,800
Aim.

781
01:01:27,880 --> 01:01:29,200
Aim!

782
01:01:29,280 --> 01:01:31,360
Shoot!

783
01:02:27,520 --> 01:02:29,320
Subtitle translation by: Panuwat Baikeawon
